Dylewo  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Grunwald, within Ostróda County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately  west of Gierzwałd (the gmina seat),  south of Ostróda, and  south-west of the regional capital Olsztyn.
During World War II, the German Nazi government operated a forced labour subcamp of the Nazi prison in Barczewo in the village.
